        </profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="5" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.CC/1–1445</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName corresp="#p_PL1" type="from">Leo
                            Pasvolsky</persName>, Special Assistant to the Secretary of State, to
                        the Counselor of the British Embassy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-17">January 17,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear <persName>Michael</persName>
                    </hi>: I wish to acknowledge the receipt of your note to me, of January 14,
                        1945,<note n="48" xml:id="d5fn1">
                        <ref target="frus1945Malta#pg_77">
                            <hi rend="italic">Conferences at Malta and Yalta</hi>, p.
                        77</ref>.</note> in which you say that His Majesty’s Government is prepared
                    to accept the President’s proposal, as communicated <pb facs="0085" n="23" xml:id="pg_23"/> to Prime Minister <persName>Churchill</persName> on
                    December 5, 1944,<note n="49" xml:id="d5fn2">See telegram 2784, December 5,
                        1944, to Moscow, <ref target="frus1945Malta#pg_58">
                            <hi rend="italic">Conferences at Malta and Yalta</hi>, p.
                        58</ref>.</note> with respect to voting in the Security Council of the
                    United Nations Organization. With respect to paragraph 1 of Chapter 8, Section
                    C, the reference is to the second sentence of that paragraph.</p>
                <p>I have been asked to tell you of the gratification which we feel at this
                    indication that the views of our two governments are in accord on this extremely
                    important question.</p>
                <p>We are bearing in mind the points covered in the third paragraph of your note
                    under reference.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Leo Pasvolsky</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
